 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Research Scientist, Computational Photography and Image Processing for AR (PhD) Facebook 621 reviews Redmond, WA Facebook 621 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description We are seeking a Research Scientist to support development of state-of-the-art deep learning algorithms for Computational Photography and Image Processing for AR/VR systems. In this role, you will be researching and developing technologies from early research concepts to products across Facebook's AR and VR products. You will be setting research directions for the projects you work on and will have the opportunities to collaborate with other researchers across Facebook AI. The ideal candidate will understand the state-of-the-art algorithms in the area of Computer Vision and/or Computational Photography, as well as how to build efficient Machine Learning models using those algorithms to run on-device. This is a full-time position. 
Enable enhanced image and video quality for AR/VR via innovative applications of Deep Learning techniques to problems such as Depth Estimation, Image Denoising, Super-Resolution, HDR, etc. 
Enable new user experiences using novel image understanding and synthesis methods based on Deep Learning 
Collaborate with cross-functional research and product teams in Computer Vision, Graphics and Machine Learning 
Design extremely efficient deep learning models that can run on head-mounted devices within limited compute and power budget 
Publish and present research at leading AI conferences and workshops 
Currently has, or is in the process of obtaining, a PhD degree or completing a postdoctoral assignment in the field of Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, Computer Vision or similar 
Must obtain work authorization in country of employment at the time of hire, and maintain ongoing work authorization during employment 
1+ years hands-on experience in deep learning algorithms and techniques, e.g., convolutional neural networks (CNN), recurrent networks (RNN) and/or related areas 
Interpersonal experience: cross-group and cross-culture collaboration 
2+ years of industry or university experience in projects in areas such as computational photography and/or computer vision 
Proven track record of achieving results as demonstrated by grants, fellowships, patents, as well as first-authored publications at leading workshops or conferences such as NeurIPS, ICML, CVPR, ECCV, ICCV, or similar 
